The day comes, you get bored with it enough to want to quit, which beggars the question- what do you do with your toon/money/gear?<br>
<br>
Seems like as of late, people have expressed being on the fence about this issue. Fine. We all have opinions, but there's one thing you *do* have to keep in mind-<br>
<br>
With the exception of a *few* people who would actually take a rl-purchased toon and use it the way it was meant to be used, you are a minority. The rest of those who would buy things in a game with real life money are just <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> lazy</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> people who want to look important and get attention.<br>
<br>
You take away everyone's fun, because you clearly have no idea what you are doing. You take away the fun, because you get into groups, and everone presumes that you at least have some idea of what's going on. We all make mistakes, yes, but this is different.<br>
<br>
Case in point- the Cleric (33th lev.) I was grouped with today who was running around in a set of Planar armor, not healing anyone, sending me tells that the rest of the group &quot;sucked and had no idea what they were doing&quot; and then comes the kicker- &quot;Why is everything everyone is saying coming out as gibberish?&quot; I asked him if he spoke any language beyond ((race deleted)) - said no, and was completely puzzled by this concept. This leads me to believe that this person clearly hasn't played much (if at all) before. I don't think I'm off-base in at *least* assuming this. <br>
<br>
I didn't get a response at all when I asked him *twice* where he got his armor. Lots of chatter about how everyone else in the group sucked, and the girl that was trying to get some RP going was a &quot;Roleplay loser&quot; though. Before and after I asked him this.<br>
<br>
Maybe he was twinked to the gills and PL'ed by someone. <br>
Maybe someone just *gave* him the planar armor.<br>
I don't know. I did promptly and politely leave the group when I had heard enough of it however, and I'll avoid this person like the black plague in the future.<br>
<br>
Anyhow. More to the point. Think before you sell for rl-money. <br>
Me saying &quot;don't do it&quot; or calling you &quot;scum&quot; isn't going to change this.<br>
But you are screwing other people's fun to a degree if your toon goes into the wrong hands. READ: the whole &quot;Ogah&quot; sitch that some that have had to deal with as of late. <br>
You're at your level because people assume that you've gotten there, and they depend on you to do what your class does if you're grouped. I'm an enchanter. You won't see me trying to melee, because it's pretty much a well established fact that the warrior in the group will take care of that, much like a Cleric who heals people less than the Paladin does.<br>
<br>
This is akin to putting someone in a wheelchair into a professional football league. (in comparison- you get what I'm saying). <br>
<br>
