<br>
I suspect that once people get to 60+, you'll begin to see a plethora of e-bay activity.  How to spot an e-bay on FV?  He'll be naked or undergeared to the point that you'll wonder how he managed to get to 60.  If you chat with him, you'll realize that he probably has no idea how he got to 60, too.  A bit rarer than this, but still common, are the 60's with the best non-no-drop gear around, but have never been to any of the zones where it drops and might not even know where it drops.<br>
<br>
There's not much need to worry, though.  Even the most loot-hungry d00d guild on a blue server would completely ostracize any random ebay-er.  About the only exception to this is when people know the buyer is a good player that has leveled to 60 himself.  I've seen good players buy characters for all kinds of reasons, most typically for class change or sex change (ie. tired of cross-dressing -- seen both men and women do this to play gender-aligned characters). <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
